Package net.visualcoding.ts3serverquery

Provides the classes necessary to interact with the TS3 Server Query interface.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    TS3EventListener
    The TS3EventListener interface provides the necessary methods that an event listener needs to implement in order to listen for events from the TS3 Server.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    TS3EventThread
    This thread listens for events and executes them all under a single thread.
    TS3InputThread
    This class implements at thread that listens for input from the Teamspeak 3 Server.
    TS3Map
    This class provides a map structure suitable for TS3 Server Query queries.
    TS3PollingThread
    This thread polls the TS3 server to find newly connected clients, disconnected clients, and clients that have moved channels.
    TS3Reader
    TS3Reader, this class is simply a wrapper over the BufferedReader that overwrites the readLine() method to handle responses from the TS3 Server Query.
    TS3Result
    This class is a container for the TS3 Server Query responses.
    TS3ServerQueryClient
    TS3ServerQuery is a low-level interface for communicating with a Teamspeak 3 server through the Teamspeak 3 Server Query.
    TS3ServerQueryClientExample  
    TS3Writer
    TS3Writer class extends the BufferedWriter class and overwrites the newLine() method to return the line-endings used in the TS3 Server Query.
